Alternative subobject display for chapters: one bordered card per
chapter instead of one shared wikitable. Used by Category:ReviewedBook
via a field-level `has_subobject_display_template = ChapterCards`
override on the Chapter subobject field. This wins over Chapter's own
category-level default (`Has subobject display template = ChapterTable`).

Side-by-side comparison on the fixture wiki:
* [[The Hobbit]] (Category:Book) - chapters render via ChapterTable
  (subobject-category default) - one shared wikitable.
* [[Dune]] (Category:ReviewedBook) - chapters render via ChapterCards
  (field-level override) - one green-bordered card per chapter.

Empty-case suppression: `format=template` with no rows emits nothing,
same as ChapterTable's `introtemplate`/`outrotemplate` idiom.

Parameters:
* category - Subobject category name (defaults to "Chapter").
* page     - Parent page to read chapters from (defaults to
             {{FULLPAGENAME}}).
</noinclude>
